name: Dairy Farm Nature Park

name: Dairy Farm Nature Park
review_text:
From Hillview MRT station Exit A walked up bit will be in front of Dairy Farm Outdoor Adventure Learning Centre turn left to Dairy Farm Nature Park. Turn right to Singapore Quarry. Have attached photos. Didn't try the Wallace Trail.

There's a Wallace Education Centre which transformed from a cowshed. Can learned the history of Dairy Farm Nature Park from here. It is a permanent exhibition of biogeography and biodiversity in the region. It's also named after famous English naturalist Alfred Russel Wallace who contributed to the development of natural science and used to study the natural history of the Malay Archipelago in the 1800s. An interactive exhibits with information about insects and wildlife in the area. There are also 3D models, a video game, a trick-eye wall.

The Dairy Farm Quarry is around 700m from the starting point and it takes me about 15mins walk to reach. Dairy Farm Quarry is unlike most other quarries you find in Singapore. While most quarries are turned into lakes, this one is filled up with earth after its granite quarrying operations stopped.

name: Dairy Farm Nature Park
review_text:
I am so in love with this place. This is where a city boy who is tired of the bustling city life would escape to to be with nature. I never realised about this place until recently and I am more than grateful I took a trip down from the other end of Singapore to check it out. Trails were very well-defined with signs every now and then, and when I went in the morning, the sun casting the shadows around looked so amazing! I also spotted some hints of rock climbing which I suspect to be a regular activity here. Mountain bikers all around too, wheezing pass every 10 minutes of so.

I really hope they don't fence this place up to create a pavement, or to restrict exploration, like the other side of the quarry.

name: Dairy Farm Nature Park
review_text:
One of my favourite parks. For first timer, go for the easier trail, ie to the Singapore Quarry.

Approx 2.5km (30mins walk) to and fro Car Park A/ Hillview MRT and Singapore Quarry. On your way back to car park/Hillview MRT, there is a path leading to Rail Mall via Fuyong interim playground. This path is 600m from the quarry. You can get your breakfast/tea at Springleaf prata / Nam Kee Pau / Subway / Toastbox / Eat / Sunnychoice vegetarian cafe / cat cafe, etc there.

For those looking for a laid back vibe, head to Wallace Trail.

For those looking for a more challenging hike, try Dairy Farm Loop. NParks classified it as a difficult trail. It is indeed difficult for me due to its steep and seemingly endless steps. Personally, I think it is more challenging than Bukit Timah Nature Reserve steep steps. Approx 4km if you were to start from Hillview station, head towards Wallace Trail, up to North View Hut via Dairy Farm Loop (Upper) to the summit and down to Bukit Timah Reserve Visitor Centre. Took me approx 1.5hr to complete the walk. You can head to Cheong Chin Nam Road / Beauty World Level 4 food centre / Bukit Timah Food Centre for Makan after the walk. Dairy Farm Loop has been closed from 25 August 2021 until further notice. Went there on 6 Jan 2022 and it is still closed.

name: Dairy Farm Nature Park
review_text:
This hidden jem has a different kind of natural beauty for all.
Its at Walking distance from Railmall.
Nearest MRT : HillView MRT

Its beauty increases even more during rainy day.
Good for short hiking. At the end, you can rest at beautiful Singapore Quarry Lake and enjoy natural beauty.
Can spend there hours watching Colourful Fishes and Turtles .
I loved soothing Cricket and Bird sounds.
A great place for meditation.
My kid love to go there mainly to see colorful fishes and turtles.

While returning she enjoys playing in playground beside Railmall.
Apart from hiking, if you love Mountain Biking, then there is Mountain biking trails as well, surrounded by forest. It goes all the way towards Bukit Timah and connects through Park Connectors.
Entry point is very close to Rail Corridors end point near Rail mall.
Usually when I want a relaxing short hiking after I finish my rail corridor bike rides, I simply choose this option.
At Railmall, there are lot of eateries and shops, where you can have your breakfast and lunch after ride.

Only missing thing I observed there is, no arrangements for Drinking water and toilets, so make sure to carry some water before starting.

name: Dairy Farm Nature Park
review_text:
Out of this world and into the jungle that was once a cow-covered dairy hill!
Incredible immersive experience on how  plant and animal life can reclaim their realms!
Experience this park by being prepared and you will love it here!! Dress for the heat, humidity and insects. Wear bug repellent. Watch where you step. Bring water. Wear sunscreen and/or wear technical fabrics designed for this kind of environment and you'll be fine.
Best things: a bazillion butterflies, squirrels all over, birds hiding in the canopy, old ruins to explore, history, interesting trees like durian and bananas among others...and so many flowers! good trails (and a place to rinse off muddy shoes afterwards), perfect place for photographers. Not crowded.  Mysterious shadows and glimmering sunlit patches to explore.
Notes: Flip flops not okay here. Sturdy shoes really are needed. Not recommended for very young children or strollers...at least not on the Wallace Trail and some other trails in the Dairy Farm/Bukit Timah Nature Reserve wilds. Consider bringing gloves and a trash bag and pick up garbage left behind by others. There is not a lot of trash, but enough that it needs attention and removal.
Most of all, wow! I love this place. What a gem!!

name: Dairy Farm Nature Park
review_text:
Dairy Farm Nature Park is connected to the Bukit Timah Nature Reserve. The access points are near the Bukit Timah Perak and from Wallace Trail (off Dairy Farm Road).

The primary trail is known as the Dairy Farm Loop, consisting of paved paths and steps. It takes about 35 minutes to 1.5 hours to complete the loop, depending on your fitness level.

Because the step heights are not uniform and some sections are steep, your heart rate and go up quickly. You might want to pace yourself, especially during your first attempt.

Like anything else, it gets easier in your subsequent attempts.

review_text:
(Translated by Google) Off to the jungle... And that with the S-Bahn. Where is that? Well in Singapore.

A great experience where you can observe countless animals and plants and really feel like you are in the jungle. And all this at no cost.

With such little jewels, you can experience many great things in Singapore without having to pay a lot of money. Thanks for this beautiful place!

(Original)
Ab in den Dschungel… Und das mit der S-Bahn. Wo geht das schon? Na in Singapur.

Ein tolles Erlebnis, bei dem ihr zahllose Tiere und Pflanzen beobachten und euch so richtig im Urwald fühlen könnt. Und das alles ohne Kosten.

Mit solchen kleinen Juwelen kann man in Singapur viele tolle Dinge erleben, ohne dass es teuer werden muss. Danke für diesen schönen Ort!
